This is probably okay.  Some notes below:

`AccessModifier.PROTECTED` doesn't make a lot of sense since `Immutable` classes are final. Another option would be to also drop package private and switch to just a Boolean `privateConstructors` but I think having a general purpose enum is probably going to be more consistent in the long run if we need this capability in other places later, so I'd probably just leave it.

Currently you can use `@Immutable` in conjunction with `@Builder`, e.g.:
```
@Immutable @Builder(builderStrategy=InitializerStrategy)
class Person { String name }
def john = new Person(Person.createInitializer().name('John'))
```
I'd just note that the current PR doesn't change the visibility of the constructor supplied by `@Builder`. We could make the Builder transform peak into the Immutable definition or perhaps instead have an independent marker annotation that builder, immutable, canonical, MapConstructor, TupleConstructor etc. could look for, e.g. `@Constructor(visibility=Visibility.PRIVATE)` or `@Visibility(constructor=Visibility.PRIVATE)`.

